Re: URI-scheme for bitcoin

Bitcointalk

2010-06-16 00:15:47 UTC - [11]Original Post

   [12]http://127.0.0.1:8330/?to=domain.com&amount=200.00&comment=order_12
   345
   or
   [13]http://127.0.0.1:8330/?to=<bitcoinaddress><separatorchar>1.2.3.4&am
   ount=200.00
   But as long as the link is already doing the typing for you, I donʼt
   see much benefit in using a domain address instead of bitcoin address.
    With a bitcoin address, the user canʼt send an unidentified payment.
   They canʼt send payment until theyʼve been given a correct bitcoin
   address to send to.
   What would be nice about sending by domain is you could visually verify
   who itʼs going to.
   A more crucial issue is what if the browser isnʼt allowed to connect to
   127.0.0.1:
   [14]http://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=63.msg1589#msg1589
   and if thatʼs true, then what about that example freenet link that had
   127.0.0.1 in it?
